{
  "text": "Experimental measurements have shown that bow squat is greater in magnitude than trim; thus it has more effect on grounding. It has been observed that the variation of squat follows the same trend for various ship types although the magnitude differs from slender to full forms. The results portray that full form ships such as tankers trim more by the bow than the slender hull forms. If a ship moves forward with a very high speed in shallow water, then grounding due to excessive squat could occur at the bow or at the stern. Therefore, location of maximum squat can be explained as follows [CITATION_1] :",
